From bccca68c136facee215dc1d4bb7d03402641110a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ahmed Adan <ahmed.adan@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 20:13:30 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] linux: backport overlayfs fsverity loaded check fix

Backport of [FROM-ML] fix for f77f281b6118 ('fsverity: use a hashtable
to find the fsverity_info') which broke ovl_ensure_verity_loaded when
the inode was not in core. This breaks bootc on the v7.0.1 kernel.

Upstream-Status: Submitted
Link: https://github.com/bootc-dev/bootc/issues/2174
Link: https://github.com/OpenGamingCollective/linux/commit/a9abecad80c9f0ca0e6ab4243158a349f102e6a3
---
 ...-overlayfs-fix-fsverity-loaded-check.patch | 32 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 32 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 patches/linux/0002-overlayfs-fix-fsverity-loaded-check.patch

diff --git a/patches/linux/0002-overlayfs-fix-fsverity-loaded-check.patch b/patches/linux/0002-overlayfs-fix-fsverity-loaded-check.patch
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..b94aa59c5
--- /dev/null
+++ b/patches/linux/0002-overlayfs-fix-fsverity-loaded-check.patch
@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@
+From a9abecad80c9f0ca0e6ab4243158a349f102e6a3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
+From: Colin Walters <walters@verbum.org>
+Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 16:05:44 -0700
+Subject: [PATCH] [FROM-ML] Commit f77f281b6118 ("fsverity: use a hashtable to
+ find the fsverity_info") that broke `ovl_ensure_verity_loaded` in the case
+ when the inode was not in core.
+
+The APIs here are in my opinion now confusing, but this patch intentionally
+aims for a minimized fix by using `fsverity_get_info()` which ensures
+the hash table is loaded.
+
+Fixes: f77f281b6118 ("fsverity: use a hashtable to find the fsverity_info")
+Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
+Link: https://github.com/bootc-dev/bootc/issues/2174
+Signed-off-by: Colin Walters <walters@verbum.org>
+---
+ fs/overlayfs/util.c | 2 +-
+ 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)
+
+diff --git a/fs/overlayfs/util.c b/fs/overlayfs/util.c
+index 2ea769f311c34..5a2a09c15036d 100644
+--- a/fs/overlayfs/util.c
++++ b/fs/overlayfs/util.c
+@@ -1379,7 +1379,7 @@ int ovl_ensure_verity_loaded(const struct path *datapath)
+ 	struct inode *inode = d_inode(datapath->dentry);
+ 	struct file *filp;
+ 
+-	if (!fsverity_active(inode) && IS_VERITY(inode)) {
++	if (IS_VERITY(inode) && !fsverity_get_info(inode)) {
+ 		/*
+ 		 * If this inode was not yet opened, the verity info hasn't been
+ 		 * loaded yet, so we need to do that here to force it into memory.
-- 
2.54.0

